WEBVTT

00:03.876 --> 00:05.292
So, Jessie,

00:06.042 --> 00:07.542
what do you think?

00:07.584 --> 00:09.250
- I think this
- is amazing!

00:09.292 --> 00:10.334
So, that's a yes?

00:10.375 --> 00:12.209
It's also really sudden!

00:12.250 --> 00:13.417
So, that's a no?

00:13.459 --> 00:14.938
No! I mean, it's just

00:14.939 --> 00:16.417
amazingly sudden!

00:16.459 --> 00:17.626
And suddenly amazing!

00:18.709 --> 00:20.042
Am I babbling?

00:20.083 --> 00:21.230
(CHUCKLES) A little,

00:21.231 --> 00:22.375
but you're really cute

00:20.083 --> 00:22.375
doing it.

00:22.417 --> 00:23.626
(CHUCKLES)

00:23.667 --> 00:25.647
Brooks, I'm flattered

00:25.648 --> 00:27.626
and thrilled,

00:27.667 --> 00:29.351
- but, we've only - known each other
- A few months.

00:29.375 --> 00:31.209
Hey, it's okay,

00:31.210 --> 00:33.042
I know it's

00:29.375 --> 00:33.042
a huge decision,

00:33.083 --> 00:34.351
- so if you need - some time to
- Think it over...

00:34.375 --> 00:35.709
Yes, some time.

00:35.710 --> 00:37.042
Perfect. Thank you.

00:37.083 --> 00:38.834
- Great, I'll be back
- in five minutes.

00:38.876 --> 00:40.500
What?

00:40.542 --> 00:41.834
- (CHUCKLES)
- I'm kidding.

00:41.876 --> 00:43.000
(SIGHS) Oh...

00:47.083 --> 00:48.042
I love you.

00:48.083 --> 00:49.083
I love you, too.

00:53.375 --> 00:54.375
(ELEVATOR DINGS)

00:58.083 --> 01:00.042
Whoa!

01:00.083 --> 01:02.063
A dimly lit room

01:02.064 --> 01:04.042
filled with flower

01:00.083 --> 01:04.042
petals.

01:04.083 --> 01:05.542
This must be what

01:05.543 --> 01:07.000
the inside of Emma's

01:04.083 --> 01:07.000
brain looks like.

01:09.083 --> 01:10.272
Plus, there'd be

01:10.273 --> 01:11.459
glitter and shoes.

01:09.083 --> 01:11.459
(CHUCKLES)

01:12.792 --> 01:13.918
So, I assume that

01:13.919 --> 01:15.042
these scented candles

01:15.083 --> 01:16.688
and roses are some

01:16.689 --> 01:18.292
lame romantic gesture

01:15.083 --> 01:18.292
by Brooks?

01:18.334 --> 01:21.042
No. No, let's just say...

01:21.083 --> 01:23.063
Bertram's bathroom is

01:23.064 --> 01:25.042
a little too close to the

01:21.083 --> 01:25.042
living room for my taste.

01:25.083 --> 01:26.626
Oh, no, that was me.

01:29.083 --> 01:30.563
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh

01:30.564 --> 01:32.042
Oh, oh, oh, oh

01:32.083 --> 01:35.667
♪ Hey Jessie, hey Jessie

01:35.709 --> 01:37.376
♪ It feels like a party

01:37.377 --> 01:39.042
every day

01:39.083 --> 01:42.709
♪ Hey Jessie, hey Jessie

01:42.751 --> 01:44.626
♪ But they keep on pulling

01:44.627 --> 01:46.500
me every which way

01:46.542 --> 01:49.751
♪ Hey Jessie, hey Jessie

01:49.792 --> 01:51.418
♪ My whole world is changing

01:51.419 --> 01:53.042
Turning around

01:53.083 --> 01:55.042
♪ They got me going crazy

01:55.043 --> 01:57.000
Yeah, they're shaking

01:53.083 --> 01:57.000
the ground

01:57.042 --> 01:58.938
♪ But they took a chance

01:58.939 --> 02:00.834
on the new girl in town

02:00.876 --> 02:02.460
♪ And I don't want to let them

02:02.461 --> 02:04.042
down, down, down

02:04.083 --> 02:07.792
♪ Hey Jessie

02:07.834 --> 02:11.375
♪ Hey Jessie

02:11.417 --> 02:13.230
♪ It feels like a party

02:13.231 --> 02:15.042
every day

02:15.083 --> 02:17.001
♪ Hey, hey, hey,

02:17.002 --> 02:18.918
hey, hey, Jessie ♪

02:22.959 --> 02:24.000
Aha!

02:26.125 --> 02:27.563
Pay up! You were wrong!

02:27.564 --> 02:29.000
I did get proposed

02:26.125 --> 02:29.000
to before Zuri!

02:30.626 --> 02:32.042
Now, we've been over this,

02:32.083 --> 02:33.334
if it's yelled from

02:33.335 --> 02:34.584
a construction site,

02:32.083 --> 02:34.584
it doesn't count.

02:37.000 --> 02:38.000
No!

02:38.584 --> 02:41.042
I mean, Brooks proposed.

02:41.083 --> 02:42.563
Oh, congratulations!

02:42.564 --> 02:44.042
Did you tell

02:41.083 --> 02:44.042
the kids yet?

02:44.083 --> 02:45.563
I can't. I mean,

02:45.564 --> 02:47.042
they're so anti-Brooks.

02:47.083 --> 02:48.584
Bertram,

02:48.626 --> 02:50.626
I love him so much,

02:50.667 --> 02:51.730
but I told him

02:51.731 --> 02:52.792
I needed more time

02:50.667 --> 02:52.792
to decide.

02:52.834 --> 02:53.939
Well, it is a very

02:53.940 --> 02:55.042
important decision.

02:52.834 --> 02:55.042
(SIGHS)

02:55.083 --> 02:56.435
- You're sure
- he's the perfect guy?

02:56.459 --> 02:57.751
Of course!

02:57.752 --> 02:59.042
Other than the kids

02:56.459 --> 02:59.042
not liking him,

02:59.083 --> 03:00.918
- and his mom
- hating me...

03:00.959 --> 03:03.043
Don't forget, his jaw

03:03.044 --> 03:05.125
makes that clicking noise

03:00.959 --> 03:05.125
when he eats.

03:05.167 --> 03:06.605
Good luck living

03:06.606 --> 03:08.042
with that for

03:05.167 --> 03:08.042
the rest of your life.

03:09.042 --> 03:10.042
You hear it, too?

03:10.083 --> 03:11.876
Everyone hears it.

03:14.083 --> 03:16.000
- I was so happy
- when I came out here.

03:18.083 --> 03:19.667
Glad I could help!

03:24.584 --> 03:25.626
Hey, Jessie.

03:25.667 --> 03:27.000
- I'm fine!
- (GASPING)

03:27.042 --> 03:28.727
- I've nothing going on
- in my life right now

03:28.751 --> 03:29.835
Besides carving this

03:29.836 --> 03:30.918
Halloween pumpkin.

03:31.876 --> 03:33.500
- We could have
- told you that.

03:35.083 --> 03:36.810
- Do you guys want to try
- carving a pumpkin?

03:36.834 --> 03:38.143
- It'll definitely be
- better than mine.

03:38.167 --> 03:39.334
(GASPS) I think I made

03:39.335 --> 03:40.500
the mouth too big.

03:45.667 --> 03:47.042
- Sure. I'll give it
- a shot.

03:47.083 --> 03:49.042
Hmm.

03:49.083 --> 03:51.042
- Why do you
- carry around gloves?

03:51.083 --> 03:53.063
You never know

03:53.064 --> 03:55.042
when you're about to

03:51.083 --> 03:55.042
enter a nail danger zone.

03:55.083 --> 03:57.042
- Or if Luke touched
- a doorknob before you.

03:58.751 --> 04:01.042
Jessie, this is Farfel.

04:01.083 --> 04:03.042
- I am babysitting him
- for Zoey,

04:03.083 --> 04:04.751
A cute girl at school.

04:04.792 --> 04:06.667
JESSIE: Oh!

04:06.709 --> 04:08.209
Good call, every guy knows

04:08.210 --> 04:09.709
the way to a girl's heart

04:06.709 --> 04:09.709
is through her rodent.

04:09.751 --> 04:11.042
(CHUCKLES)

04:11.083 --> 04:12.563
Then, when Zoey

04:12.564 --> 04:14.042
is putty in my hands,

04:14.083 --> 04:15.563
I will propose

04:15.564 --> 04:17.041
we go on a date.

04:14.083 --> 04:17.041
Whoa!

04:17.083 --> 04:18.397
What is it with all

04:18.398 --> 04:19.709
the proposals lately?

04:20.750 --> 04:21.938
Uh, Jessie,

04:21.939 --> 04:23.125
is everything okay?

04:23.167 --> 04:24.334
Yeah, yeah, yeah,

04:24.335 --> 04:25.500
I'm fine.

04:27.083 --> 04:28.125
Why... Why do you ask?

04:28.167 --> 04:29.334
Because your face

04:29.335 --> 04:30.500
looks like this.

04:35.959 --> 04:38.876
Wow, you are good.

04:38.918 --> 04:40.718
- I should really get
- that mole checked out.

04:44.292 --> 04:45.668
Wow, look what

04:45.669 --> 04:47.042
they're doing for

04:44.292 --> 04:47.042
the Halloween festival.

04:47.083 --> 04:48.688
Hey, they're having

04:48.689 --> 04:50.292
a pumpkin carving contest!

04:50.334 --> 04:51.563
And first prize

04:51.564 --> 04:52.792
is a tiara?

04:52.834 --> 04:53.918
I should go over there now

04:53.919 --> 04:55.000
and give them my head

04:52.834 --> 04:55.000
measurements.

04:57.292 --> 04:59.168
So, Luke,

04:59.169 --> 05:01.042
want to go to

04:57.292 --> 05:01.042
the Haunted House?

05:01.083 --> 05:03.042
Or are you scared?

05:03.083 --> 05:05.042
Me? Scared?

05:05.083 --> 05:07.000
- I don't even know
- the meaning of the word.

05:07.042 --> 05:08.521
Considering your

05:08.522 --> 05:10.000
terrible vocab scores,

05:07.042 --> 05:10.000
that's a real possibility.

05:13.125 --> 05:14.125
So...

05:14.667 --> 05:16.042
Jessie,

05:16.083 --> 05:17.268
- have you made
- a decision yet?

05:17.292 --> 05:19.042
I still don't know.

05:19.083 --> 05:20.563
I mean,

05:20.564 --> 05:22.042
we're both so young.

05:19.083 --> 05:22.042
I'm 22, you're 25...

05:22.083 --> 05:23.959
- Yeah, but we're both
- animal lovers.

05:24.000 --> 05:25.022
So, we're like 150

05:25.023 --> 05:26.042
in dog years.

05:27.375 --> 05:28.813
Look, I just...

05:28.814 --> 05:30.250
I wanna make sure that

05:27.375 --> 05:30.250
we consider everything.

05:30.292 --> 05:32.042
You know like...

05:32.083 --> 05:34.059
- I kinda wish you - and the kids got along
- A little better.

05:34.083 --> 05:36.042
- Oh, what do you mean?
- The kids love me!

05:36.083 --> 05:37.334
Oh!

05:37.375 --> 05:39.042
(LAUGHING)

05:39.083 --> 05:40.292
Kids!

05:40.334 --> 05:42.918
(ALL WHISTLING INNOCENTLY)

05:42.959 --> 05:43.980
Do you have

05:43.981 --> 05:45.000
something to say

05:42.959 --> 05:45.000
to Brooks?

05:45.042 --> 05:46.125
Heads up?

05:46.167 --> 05:47.834
(LAUGHING)

05:50.083 --> 05:52.042
Whoa!

05:52.083 --> 05:54.397
That pumpkin is

05:54.398 --> 05:56.709
the spitting image

05:52.083 --> 05:56.709
of Andrew Garfield.

05:56.751 --> 05:58.043
It's like his

05:58.044 --> 05:59.334
decapitated head is

05:56.751 --> 05:59.334
right here with us.

05:59.375 --> 06:00.959
I wish!

06:02.042 --> 06:03.042
It took me forever to...

06:03.083 --> 06:04.918
(GASPING)

06:07.083 --> 06:09.042
Oh, no! Emma,

06:09.083 --> 06:11.042
I am so sorry.

06:11.083 --> 06:12.563
You destroyed Pumpkin

06:12.564 --> 06:14.042
Andrew Garfield!

06:14.083 --> 06:15.522
You better hope

06:15.523 --> 06:16.959
Pumpkin Emma Stone

06:14.083 --> 06:16.959
doesn't find you!

06:19.209 --> 06:20.646
So, how's the cute

06:20.647 --> 06:22.083
little guy doing?

06:22.125 --> 06:24.000
I am fine, thank you.

06:25.042 --> 06:26.310
- (STUTTERING)
- I meant the hamster.

06:26.334 --> 06:28.167
- Oh, so what am I,
- chopped liver?

06:28.209 --> 06:29.334
Uh...

06:29.375 --> 06:31.125
- I need to get
- Farfel some food.

06:31.167 --> 06:32.167
Will you watch him

06:32.168 --> 06:33.168
for a moment?

06:33.209 --> 06:35.042
- Sure.
- Thank you.

06:35.083 --> 06:36.480
I hate your boyfriend!

06:36.481 --> 06:37.876
Look at what he did to me!

06:37.918 --> 06:39.709
- JESSIE: I'm sure
- it was an accident.

06:39.751 --> 06:41.292
Besides, if you ask me,

06:41.334 --> 06:43.127
you are making those

06:43.128 --> 06:44.918
pumpkin guts work.

06:41.334 --> 06:44.918
(SNAPS FINGER)

06:44.959 --> 06:46.792
- Brooks might be
- a little klutzy,

06:46.834 --> 06:47.939
But I find him to be

06:47.940 --> 06:49.042
a nice enough fellow.

06:49.083 --> 06:50.522
Ravi, either there is

06:50.523 --> 06:51.959
something is wrong

06:49.083 --> 06:51.959
with Farfel,

06:52.000 --> 06:53.959
- or he's really good
- at freeze tag!

06:55.083 --> 06:56.334
(BOTH GASPING)

06:56.375 --> 06:58.126
You monster!

06:58.127 --> 06:59.876
You have killed Farfel,

06:59.918 --> 07:01.397
and my only shot at

07:01.398 --> 07:02.876
true love with Zoey!

07:02.918 --> 07:03.980
See? This is

07:03.981 --> 07:05.042
what he does.

07:05.083 --> 07:07.000
He ruins everything!

07:07.042 --> 07:08.083
(GROANS)

07:09.083 --> 07:10.167
(SIGHS)

07:11.083 --> 07:13.083
This is terrible!

07:13.125 --> 07:14.584
I remember

07:14.585 --> 07:16.042
how I felt when

07:13.125 --> 07:16.042
my hamster died.

07:16.083 --> 07:17.918
- I left him with
- my mother, and...

07:17.959 --> 07:18.980
Ah! Say no more.

07:18.981 --> 07:20.000
I would have jumped off

07:17.959 --> 07:20.000
my little wheel, too.

07:26.375 --> 07:28.272
Emma, for the last time,

07:28.273 --> 07:30.167
there is no princess in

07:26.375 --> 07:30.167
"Frankenstein."

07:30.209 --> 07:31.792
There is now.

07:33.834 --> 07:35.439
You know, when you

07:35.440 --> 07:37.042
asked me to be the

07:33.834 --> 07:37.042
village Burgermeister,

07:37.083 --> 07:38.563
I thought there would be

07:38.564 --> 07:40.042
actual burgers involved.

07:40.083 --> 07:41.918
- If it helps,
- they have corndogs.

07:41.959 --> 07:43.600
- It always helps
- if they have corndogs!

07:45.876 --> 07:47.001
Uh, Ravi,

07:47.002 --> 07:48.125
just so you know,

07:48.167 --> 07:50.042
this festival isn't really

07:50.083 --> 07:51.083
a "bring your own

07:51.084 --> 07:52.083
dead hamster"

07:50.083 --> 07:52.083
kind of shindig.

07:53.125 --> 07:54.959
No.

07:55.000 --> 07:56.460
Like Dr. Frankenstein,

07:56.461 --> 07:57.918
I shall use electricity

07:57.959 --> 07:59.021
to bring the dead

07:59.022 --> 08:00.083
back to life.

08:00.125 --> 08:02.230
I shall harness

08:02.231 --> 08:04.334
lightning via a kite,

08:00.125 --> 08:04.334
and re-direct it to Farfel,

08:04.375 --> 08:05.751
thus reanimating

08:05.752 --> 08:07.125
his little heart.

08:07.167 --> 08:09.084
This is why you have

08:09.085 --> 08:11.000
to babysit hamsters

08:07.167 --> 08:11.000
to get girls.

08:13.042 --> 08:14.042
Hey, Luke,

08:14.083 --> 08:15.730
while Dr. Dorkenstein

08:15.731 --> 08:17.375
is flying his kite,

08:17.417 --> 08:18.668
want to go into

08:18.669 --> 08:19.918
the Haunted House?

08:19.959 --> 08:21.210
Those kids back there

08:21.211 --> 08:22.459
gave it two severed

08:19.959 --> 08:22.459
thumbs up.

08:24.584 --> 08:26.042
No, thanks.

08:26.083 --> 08:27.209
It looks lame.

08:27.250 --> 08:28.959
(SCREAMING)

08:31.083 --> 08:32.250
- (WHINING)
- Super lame.

08:34.082 --> 08:35.542
Every time you lie,

08:35.543 --> 08:37.000
your hump grows a little.

08:39.167 --> 08:41.208
How can you date a guy

08:41.210 --> 08:43.250
who killed my pumpkin

08:39.167 --> 08:43.250
and Ravi's hamster?

08:43.292 --> 08:45.042
- You're blinded
- by his pretty face.

08:45.083 --> 08:46.083
I'm not.

08:46.125 --> 08:47.147
He's sweet

08:47.148 --> 08:48.167
and thoughtful

08:48.209 --> 08:49.564
and always knows

08:49.565 --> 08:50.918
exactly what to say to

08:48.209 --> 08:50.918
make my heart melt.

08:52.292 --> 08:55.000
Hmm. Corndog good.

08:58.083 --> 09:00.000
Yep. He's a charmer.

09:02.125 --> 09:03.188
Hey, Luke.

09:03.189 --> 09:04.250
I got us tickets

09:02.125 --> 09:04.250
or the Haunted House.

09:04.292 --> 09:05.602
- But...
- You can thank me later.

09:05.626 --> 09:07.375
(STAMMERING)

09:07.417 --> 09:08.980
Say hi to the

09:08.981 --> 09:10.542
ax-wielding

09:07.417 --> 09:10.542
maniac for me!

09:11.584 --> 09:12.959
(LAUGHING)

09:13.000 --> 09:15.042
That is your evil giggle.

09:15.083 --> 09:16.292
What are you up to?

09:16.334 --> 09:17.709
I told Brooks

09:17.710 --> 09:19.083
he can win

09:16.334 --> 09:19.083
Luke over

09:19.125 --> 09:20.334
by taking him into

09:20.335 --> 09:21.542
the Haunted House.

09:19.125 --> 09:21.542
(CHUCKLES)

09:21.584 --> 09:23.083
Two dorks, one stone.

09:24.667 --> 09:27.584
Ah, I see. Kudos.

09:27.626 --> 09:29.125
(SCREAMING)

09:29.167 --> 09:31.167
Luke, I'm so sorry.

09:31.209 --> 09:32.605
I had no idea

09:32.606 --> 09:34.000
you'd get so scared

09:31.209 --> 09:34.000
you'd puke.

09:38.083 --> 09:40.042
When did you have corn?

09:40.083 --> 09:42.042
(LAUGHING)

09:42.083 --> 09:44.042
I feel horrible.

09:44.083 --> 09:46.059
- Is there anything - I can do to make it
- Up to you?

09:46.083 --> 09:47.126
Don't you think you've

09:47.127 --> 09:48.167
ruined Halloween enough

09:46.083 --> 09:48.167
for all of us?

09:50.083 --> 09:51.167
Just go away!

09:55.083 --> 09:56.126
Hey, where is

09:56.127 --> 09:57.167
Brooks going?

09:57.209 --> 09:58.626
- What did you guys
- do to him?

09:58.667 --> 09:59.814
We didn't do

09:59.815 --> 10:00.959
anything!

10:01.000 --> 10:02.626
- He made me hurl
- on the undead!

10:02.667 --> 10:04.125
- He smashed
- Andrew Garfield!

10:04.167 --> 10:06.042
He killed Farfel!

10:06.083 --> 10:08.042
- And you're supposed
- to wind up with Tony!

10:08.083 --> 10:10.125
- Well, Tony didn't propose,
- Brooks did!

10:10.167 --> 10:11.334
(ALL GASPING)

10:11.375 --> 10:12.667
He did?

10:12.709 --> 10:14.042
- Are you going
- to say yes?

10:14.083 --> 10:15.188
Maybe!

10:15.189 --> 10:16.292
I don't know!

10:16.334 --> 10:18.042
It's complicated.

10:18.083 --> 10:19.602
- I really want
- you guys to like him,

10:19.626 --> 10:20.773
But meanwhile

10:20.774 --> 10:21.918
I'm trying to figure out

10:19.626 --> 10:21.918
if I should say yes!

10:25.042 --> 10:26.146
Wow, that Haunted House

10:26.147 --> 10:27.250
is really horrifying!

10:27.292 --> 10:28.709
They had the most

10:28.710 --> 10:30.125
realistic vomit

10:27.292 --> 10:30.125
I have ever seen.

10:37.083 --> 10:38.083
Hey, Luke...

10:39.083 --> 10:40.083
What?

10:41.083 --> 10:42.772
You see those

10:42.773 --> 10:44.459
girls over there?

10:44.500 --> 10:46.272
They want to go

10:46.273 --> 10:48.042
in the Haunted House,

10:44.500 --> 10:48.042
but they're scared, too.

10:48.083 --> 10:49.083
So now you're

10:49.084 --> 10:50.084
calling me a girl?

10:50.125 --> 10:51.626
Salt in the wound, bro.

10:52.709 --> 10:54.709
No! What I'm saying is,

10:54.751 --> 10:56.459
that since there are no

10:56.460 --> 10:58.167
scary surprises left

10:54.751 --> 10:58.167
for you in there,

10:58.209 --> 10:59.605
you can be

10:59.606 --> 11:01.000
the brave shoulder

10:58.209 --> 11:01.000
that they lean on.

11:02.209 --> 11:03.292
LUKE: Oh!

11:03.334 --> 11:05.042
Nice!

11:05.083 --> 11:07.000
- Thanks, bro. - Ow's my hump look?
- Oh.

