See, this is why

16:26.398 --> 16:27.751
we can't have

16:25.042 --> 16:27.751
nice things!

16:28.709 --> 16:30.063
Quick! Someone get

16:30.064 --> 16:31.417
the authorities!

16:31.459 --> 16:33.250
- You are
- the authorities!

16:33.292 --> 16:34.980
Oh, um, well,

16:34.981 --> 16:36.667
I would stop him but

16:36.709 --> 16:38.126
I feel like I have

16:38.127 --> 16:39.542
a touch of the plague

16:36.709 --> 16:39.542
coming on.

16:39.584 --> 16:40.792
Auf Wiedersehen!

16:40.834 --> 16:42.000
(ALL SCREAMING)

16:46.334 --> 16:47.667
Your boyfriend

16:47.668 --> 16:49.000
had to have

16:46.334 --> 16:49.000
super-strength!

16:49.042 --> 16:50.335
Hey, every girl wants

16:50.336 --> 16:51.626
her monster to look like

16:49.042 --> 16:51.626
he hits the gym,

16:51.667 --> 16:52.959
am I right, ladies?

16:53.000 --> 16:54.667
(GIRLS SCREAMING)

16:54.709 --> 16:55.834
Uh, perhaps we could

16:55.835 --> 16:56.959
shelve the girl talk

16:57.000 --> 16:58.959
- for when we are not
- in mortal peril!

16:59.459 --> 17:00.542
(GRUNTING)

17:02.500 --> 17:03.897
Sweetie, no, no,

17:03.898 --> 17:05.291
these are my kids!

17:05.334 --> 17:07.000
Kids good!

17:07.917 --> 17:09.626
Kids good?

17:09.666 --> 17:13.041
Yes! Kids like you.

17:13.083 --> 17:15.334
(GROANS IN AGREEMENT)

17:15.375 --> 17:17.188
Hi, Mr. Monster.

17:17.189 --> 17:19.000
Great hair.

17:20.876 --> 17:23.375
Yeah, he's smokin' hot!

17:24.041 --> 17:26.751
Smoke? Fire!

17:26.791 --> 17:28.250
- (GRUNTING)
- (PEOPLE CLAMORING)

17:29.626 --> 17:31.501
I don't understand,

17:31.502 --> 17:33.375
he was supposed to

17:29.626 --> 17:33.375
be the perfect guy!

17:33.417 --> 17:34.980
There is no

17:34.981 --> 17:36.542
such thing as

17:33.417 --> 17:36.542
the perfect guy!

17:36.584 --> 17:38.334
- Wake up and smell
- the strudel!

17:40.584 --> 17:41.876
- Strudel!
- Huh?

17:41.918 --> 17:43.500
- Strudel?
- Where? Where?

17:44.751 --> 17:46.042
I have to go.

17:46.083 --> 17:48.042
- I just realized what my
- answer to Brooks is!

17:48.083 --> 17:49.563
What? Jessie, wait.

17:49.564 --> 17:51.042
I need to know!

17:51.083 --> 17:52.563
Bertram, it's so sweet

17:52.564 --> 17:54.042
that you care,

17:54.083 --> 17:56.059
- but I can't tell you
- until after I've told Brooks.

17:56.083 --> 17:57.459
- I don't care
- if you marry him.

17:57.500 --> 17:59.000
- Just tell me where
- the strudel is!

18:03.626 --> 18:05.000
- Hey, Ravi,
- guess what?

18:06.083 --> 18:07.480
Why are your

18:07.481 --> 18:08.876
clothes smoking?

18:08.918 --> 18:10.814
My attempts to

18:10.815 --> 18:12.709
re-animate Farfel

18:08.918 --> 18:12.709
did not go as planned.

18:12.751 --> 18:13.876
However, I did discover

18:13.877 --> 18:15.000
lightning bolts

18:15.042 --> 18:17.000
- are a wonderful cure
- for constipation.

18:18.083 --> 18:20.063
Okay. Can I see

18:20.064 --> 18:22.042
Farfel for a minute?

18:22.083 --> 18:23.563
Very well.

18:23.564 --> 18:25.042
You may pay

18:22.083 --> 18:25.042
your respects,

18:25.083 --> 18:26.751
but make it quick.

18:26.792 --> 18:27.856
Thanks to you,

18:27.857 --> 18:28.918
he has a date

18:26.792 --> 18:28.918
with a shoebox

18:28.959 --> 18:30.000
and a shallow hole.

18:37.083 --> 18:39.042
Hey there, little buddy.

18:39.083 --> 18:41.042
- (GASPING)
- He is alive!

18:41.083 --> 18:42.542
He is alive!

18:42.543 --> 18:44.000
How did you do it?

18:44.042 --> 18:45.542
I called my

18:45.543 --> 18:47.042
top veterinarian at

18:44.042 --> 18:47.042
the animal sanctuary.

18:47.083 --> 18:48.313
She told me when

18:48.314 --> 18:49.542
hamsters get too cold,

18:47.083 --> 18:49.542
they hibernate.

18:49.584 --> 18:50.814
Oh, Farfel must have

18:50.815 --> 18:52.042
gotten too chilly

18:52.083 --> 18:53.792
- when I took him
- to the terrace!

18:53.834 --> 18:54.897
Undone by

18:54.898 --> 18:55.959
my own ignorance!

18:56.000 --> 18:57.188
Huh, this must be

18:57.189 --> 18:58.375
what it feels like

18:56.000 --> 18:58.375
to be Luke!

18:59.876 --> 19:01.083
(SIGHS)

19:01.125 --> 19:02.876
- Kids, can you come here
- for a second?

19:05.876 --> 19:06.876
Emma?

19:08.083 --> 19:09.083
Your Highness?

19:10.417 --> 19:11.459
Oh.

19:14.083 --> 19:15.334
Proceed.

19:16.417 --> 19:17.626
Thank you.

19:19.459 --> 19:21.042
- I have something
- to say to Brooks,

19:21.083 --> 19:23.042
- And I want you
- all to hear.

19:23.083 --> 19:24.834
Wait...

19:24.876 --> 19:26.716
- Does this mean - you have an answer
- For me?

19:28.083 --> 19:29.584
Brooks...

19:29.626 --> 19:31.584
- All my life
- I've had this image

19:31.626 --> 19:32.668
In my mind

19:32.669 --> 19:33.709
of the perfect guy,

19:33.751 --> 19:35.126
and I've been

19:35.127 --> 19:36.500
looking for him in

19:33.751 --> 19:36.500
all the wrong places.

19:36.542 --> 19:37.793
Chickaterias,

19:37.794 --> 19:39.042
Frankenstein's lab,

19:39.083 --> 19:40.897
in one instance

19:40.898 --> 19:42.709
a really shady silver mine

19:39.083 --> 19:42.709
in western Nevada.

19:43.125 --> 19:44.584
That's not important.

19:48.083 --> 19:49.542
What's important is

19:49.543 --> 19:51.000
that I finally found you

19:52.083 --> 19:54.792
and I've realized...

19:54.834 --> 19:56.375
- You're not
- the perfect guy.

19:57.751 --> 19:59.000
I'm not?

20:00.083 --> 20:01.959
No.

20:02.000 --> 20:03.522
Because there is

20:03.523 --> 20:05.042
no such thing as

20:02.000 --> 20:05.042
the perfect guy.

20:05.083 --> 20:07.063
What you are

20:07.064 --> 20:09.042
is the perfect guy

20:05.083 --> 20:09.042
for me.

20:09.083 --> 20:10.563
I know, you may have

20:10.564 --> 20:12.042
made a mess of trying to win

20:09.083 --> 20:12.042
over the kids today,

20:12.083 --> 20:14.042
- but I love
- how hard you tried.

20:14.083 --> 20:15.918
Actually,

20:15.959 --> 20:17.001
Brooks didn't make

20:17.002 --> 20:18.042
a total mess of things.

20:18.083 --> 20:20.042
- Thanks to him,
- I've been grabbed by

20:20.083 --> 20:22.000
- So many girls
- in that Haunted House,

20:22.042 --> 20:23.476
- The only thing
- I'm scared of now is

20:23.500 --> 20:24.918
- If their boyfriends
- find out!

20:25.876 --> 20:27.459
- And how can I
- dislike the man

20:27.500 --> 20:29.043
Who was so gracious

20:29.044 --> 20:30.584
when I falsely accused

20:27.500 --> 20:30.584
him of hamster-cide?

20:32.083 --> 20:33.542
And he does make

20:33.543 --> 20:35.000
a fine-looking pumpkin.

20:35.042 --> 20:36.438
Plus, he loves you

20:36.439 --> 20:37.834
almost as much as we do.

20:39.083 --> 20:41.000
Aw, thank you, guys.

20:43.083 --> 20:44.959
Zuri?

20:45.000 --> 20:46.250
Well, he seems to

20:46.251 --> 20:47.500
make you happy.

20:47.542 --> 20:48.793
And he made

20:48.794 --> 20:50.042
Luke fear-vomit,

20:47.542 --> 20:50.042
so I guess I owe him.

20:50.083 --> 20:51.792
(LAUGHING)

20:53.042 --> 20:54.042
So...

20:55.083 --> 20:56.334
Are you saying

20:56.335 --> 20:57.584
what I hope

20:55.083 --> 20:57.584
you're saying?

20:58.167 --> 20:59.500
I'm saying...

21:01.751 --> 21:03.042
- Yes, I'd love
- to marry you!

21:03.083 --> 21:04.918
(BOTH LAUGHING)

21:04.959 --> 21:06.000
(ALL CHEERING)

21:07.083 --> 21:08.834
I gather you said yes?

21:08.876 --> 21:09.960
Oh, I did.

21:09.961 --> 21:11.042
We're getting married!

21:11.083 --> 21:12.563
Oh! I'm so happy

21:12.564 --> 21:14.042
for you!

21:14.083 --> 21:16.042
- Ooh! And I have
- the perfect wedding gift.

21:16.083 --> 21:18.042
- I'll get my old
- boy band together

21:18.083 --> 21:20.042
- And we'll sing
- at your reception!

21:20.083 --> 21:21.125
Oh...

21:21.167 --> 21:22.667
- How do you feel
- about eloping?

21:26.834 --> 21:28.042
Oh, look.

21:28.083 --> 21:29.250
There's Zoey!

21:29.292 --> 21:30.626
Go give her Farfel back

21:30.627 --> 21:31.959
and then ask her out.

21:32.000 --> 21:33.167
- I will do it!
- As they say,

21:33.209 --> 21:35.042
- There is nothing
- women like

21:35.083 --> 21:37.164
- More than a man - with a freshly
- Groomed hamster.

21:39.667 --> 21:41.042
- I don't think
- anyone says that.

21:47.083 --> 21:48.083
Oh.

21:49.083 --> 21:51.042
Sorry, dude.

21:51.083 --> 21:52.126
Hey, we'll find some

21:52.127 --> 21:53.167
girls to take through

21:51.083 --> 21:53.167
the Haunted House.

21:53.209 --> 21:54.626
Somewhere around

21:54.627 --> 21:56.042
the ax-wielding maniac,

21:56.083 --> 21:57.418
they'll hold hands

21:57.419 --> 21:58.751
with anyone.

21:56.083 --> 21:58.751
(SCOFFS)

21:58.792 --> 21:59.959
I am both offended

21:59.960 --> 22:01.125
and titillated!

22:06.083 --> 22:07.397
So, girls,

22:07.398 --> 22:08.709
want to go play

22:06.083 --> 22:08.709
Whack-a-Skull?

22:08.751 --> 22:10.042
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

22:10.083 --> 22:11.563
Uh-oh, it looks like

22:11.564 --> 22:13.042
there is another

22:10.083 --> 22:13.042
storm coming.

22:13.083 --> 22:14.324
- Someone should
- tell Bertram.

22:15.167 --> 22:16.834
Whee!

22:16.876 --> 22:17.959
Look at it go!

22:19.083 --> 22:20.524
- Bertram, don't!
- That's dangerous!

22:25.083 --> 22:27.667
Ba... Burgers are ready.

